headline: Nvidia Sells Off Stake in Arm, a Company It Once Tried to Buy
summary: Nvidia unloaded 1.1 million shares, worth about $140 million based on Arm’s closing price Tuesday, according to a regulatory filing.  The disposal, which occurred sometime in the fourth quarter of last year, brings Nvidia’s stake to zero.  Nvidia declined to comment, while Arm didn’t immediately respond to a request for comment.
